column2: Why choose a Diabetes Pedigree Function of 0.2 as a key indicator for predicting Diabetes in a 65-year-old male with a BMI of 24, rather than in a 30-year-old female with a BMI of 18?
Predict(Diabetes, Age = 65, Sex = Male, BMI = 24, DPF = 0.2) > Predict(Diabetes, Age = 30, Sex = Female, Age = 18, DPF = 0.2)
